<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,476,691,750]" box="[151,397,726,750]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,257,726,750]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="41.[151,233,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[192,1331,219,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-76@41.[153,1433,175,1832]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="PLATE 1. A–H. Thagria, dorsal habitus. (A) Thagria aenigmatis, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Thagria asperitas, sp. nov., holotype; (C) Thagria biretrorsa, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Thagria colorata, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Thagria coniunctionis, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Thagria constanti, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Thagria fidelitas, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Thagria freytagi, sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261018/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Plate 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[270,389,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–14" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[250,1349,209,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@44.[231,1355,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 8–14. Thagria asperitas, sp. nov. (8) pygofer and concealed ventral process of segment X, lateral view; (9) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; (10) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view; (11) style, lateral view; (12) style, dorsal view); (13) dorsal connective and concealed ventral process of segment X, dorsobasal view; (14) subgenital plate, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261022/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 8–14</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,798,1650]" box="[151,624,798,823]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,799,823]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Length.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[250,307,798,822]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Male</collectingRegion>
7.80 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,798,1650]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,835,859]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">External morphology.</emphasis>
Moderately long, slender species. General color dark brown. Crown yellow; eyes brown; pronotum and mesontum dark brown, with light brown markings on pronotum; forewings translucent light brown, without markings (
<figureCitation box="[464,569,906,930]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="41.[151,233,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[192,1331,219,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-76@41.[153,1433,175,1832]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="PLATE 1. A–H. Thagria, dorsal habitus. (A) Thagria aenigmatis, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Thagria asperitas, sp. nov., holotype; (C) Thagria biretrorsa, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Thagria colorata, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Thagria coniunctionis, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Thagria constanti, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Thagria fidelitas, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Thagria freytagi, sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261018/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Plate 1B</figureCitation>
); face light yellow with dark brown to black markings in sutures. Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely rounded; crown broad, wider than eye width, produced about 1/ 3 entire median length, lateral margins convergent basally, disk depressed forming weak lateral carina; eyes large, slightly elongate ovoid; pronotum large, slightly longer medially than length of crown, weak, median longitudinal carina present, surface mildly rugulose; mesonotum large, slightly longer medially than length of pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, broad in anterior half, slightly convergent in distal half; clypellus short, base broad, inflated, abruptly convergent distally, apex rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,798,1650]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1158,1183]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<collectingRegion box="[199,260,1159,1183]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Male</collectingRegion>
genitalia.
</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view with short caudoventral lobe, lateral margins narrowed to rounded apex, caudodorsal margin with short, digitate lobe directed posterioventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1092,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–14" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[250,1349,209,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@44.[231,1355,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 8–14. Thagria asperitas, sp. nov. (8) pygofer and concealed ventral process of segment X, lateral view; (9) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; (10) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view; (11) style, lateral view; (12) style, dorsal view); (13) dorsal connective and concealed ventral process of segment X, dorsobasal view; (14) subgenital plate, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261022/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); segment X ventral processes concealed; aedeagus in dorsal view symmetrical, very long, about 3/4 as long as ventral paraphysis (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1422,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–14" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[250,1349,209,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@44.[231,1355,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 8–14. Thagria asperitas, sp. nov. (8) pygofer and concealed ventral process of segment X, lateral view; (9) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; (10) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view; (11) style, lateral view; (12) style, dorsal view); (13) dorsal connective and concealed ventral process of segment X, dorsobasal view; (14) subgenital plate, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261022/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs.9, 10</figureCitation>
); ventral paraphysis asymmetrical, long with 2 apical processes, each directed laterally in dorsal view, processes unequal in length (
<figureCitation box="[366,496,1302,1326]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–14" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[250,1349,209,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@44.[231,1355,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 8–14. Thagria asperitas, sp. nov. (8) pygofer and concealed ventral process of segment X, lateral view; (9) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; (10) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view; (11) style, lateral view; (12) style, dorsal view); (13) dorsal connective and concealed ventral process of segment X, dorsobasal view; (14) subgenital plate, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261022/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs.11, 12</figureCitation>
); style long, reaching to about midlength of paraphysis, very slender in distal half (Figs.12,13); connective typical; dorsal connective in dorsobasal view narrowly Y-shape, rami long. attached distally to lateral arms of segment X ventral process, stem short, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[990,1066,1374,1398]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–14" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[250,1349,209,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@44.[231,1355,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 8–14. Thagria asperitas, sp. nov. (8) pygofer and concealed ventral process of segment X, lateral view; (9) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; (10) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view; (11) style, lateral view; (12) style, dorsal view); (13) dorsal connective and concealed ventral process of segment X, dorsobasal view; (14) subgenital plate, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261022/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig.13</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate typical, tuft of long setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[374,458,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–14" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[250,1349,209,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-77@44.[231,1355,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 8–14. Thagria asperitas, sp. nov. (8) pygofer and concealed ventral process of segment X, lateral view; (9) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; (10) aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view; (11) style, lateral view; (12) style, dorsal view); (13) dorsal connective and concealed ventral process of segment X, dorsobasal view; (14) subgenital plate, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261022/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
