<subSubSection box="[199,1297,1518,1543]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,798,1650]" box="[199,1297,1518,1543]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1519,1543]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is descriptive for uneven length of the apical, ventral paraphysis processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,798,1650]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1555,1579]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
From 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang" authorityName="Zhang" authorityYear="1994" box="[389,662,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="damenglongensis">
<emphasis box="[389,584,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">damenglongensis</emphasis>
Zhang
</taxonomicName>
to which it is similar in male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NIELSON" authorityYear="2013" box="[1106,1208,1555,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asperitas">
<emphasis box="[1106,1208,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">asperitas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by the configuration of apical process of the ventral paraphysis, the narrower pygofer caudoventral lobe, shorter pygofer caudodorsal process which is directed posteriorly and by the more slender apophysis of the style.
</paragraph>
